Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a buff-coloured pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and faint traces of two lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393866) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393866)
